---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Charts">
  <p>DDF supports bar, pie, doughnut, and line charts — all defined in YAML.</p>

  <h2>Bar Chart</h2>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">- type: chart
  chart: bar
  x: 0.5
  y: 1.2
  w: 5.5
  h: 4.0
  direction: col          # col (vertical) or bar (horizontal)
  colors: [$chart1, $chart2]
  series:
    - name: "Recurring"
      labels: ["Q1", "Q2", "Q3", "Q4"]
      values: [2800, 3200, 3700, 4100]
    - name: "One-time"
      labels: ["Q1", "Q2", "Q3", "Q4"]
      values: [400, 600, 500, 800]
  style:
    gridLines: subtle
    legend: true
    legendPos: b           # t, b, l, r
    dataLabels: outEnd
    axisColor: $muted</code></pre>

  <h2>Pie Chart</h2>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">- type: chart
  chart: pie
  x: 0.5
  y: 1.2
  w: 4.5
  h: 4.0
  chartTitle: "By Segment"
  colors: [$chart1, $chart2, $chart3, $chart4]
  series:
    - name: "Segment"
      labels: ["Enterprise", "Mid-Market", "SMB", "Self-Serve"]
      values: [45, 28, 18, 9]
  style:
    showPercent: true
    legend: true
    legendPos: b</code></pre>

  <h2>Doughnut Chart</h2>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">- type: chart
  chart: doughnut
  x: 5.2
  y: 1.2
  w: 4.5
  h: 4.0
  chartTitle: "By Region"
  colors: [$chart1, $chart2, $chart3, "A78BFA"]
  series:
    - name: "Region"
      labels: ["North America", "EMEA", "APAC", "LATAM"]
      values: [52, 24, 16, 8]
  style:
    showPercent: true
    legend: true</code></pre>

  <h2>Chart Properties</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Key</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>chart</code></td><td>string</td><td><code>bar</code>, <code>pie</code>, <code>doughnut</code>, <code>line</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>direction</code></td><td>string</td><td><code>col</code> (vertical) or <code>bar</code> (horizontal). Bar charts only.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>chartTitle</code></td><td>string</td><td>Title displayed on the chart</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>colors</code></td><td>array</td><td>Series/slice colors</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>series</code></td><td>array</td><td>Data series (see below)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>style</code></td><td>object</td><td>Styling options</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Series Format</h2>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">series:
  - name: "Series Name"
    labels: ["Cat A", "Cat B", "Cat C"]
    values: [10, 20, 30]</code></pre>
  <p>Bar and line charts support multiple series. Pie and doughnut use a single series.</p>

  <h2>Style Options</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Key</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>gridLines</code></td><td><code>subtle</code> or omit for none</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>legend</code></td><td><code>true</code> / <code>false</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>legendPos</code></td><td><code>t</code>, <code>b</code>, <code>l</code>, <code>r</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>dataLabels</code></td><td><code>outEnd</code>, <code>inEnd</code>, <code>center</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>showPercent</code></td><td>Show percentage labels (pie/doughnut)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>axisColor</code></td><td>Color for axis lines</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  th, td {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    text-align: left;
  }
  th {
    background: #f1f5f9;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
